ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: necessary for students interested in medical imaging related research.
Great course for an intro to imaging. I would definitely recommend to any BME student even remotely interested in imaging, as this course provides a solid background of some of the basics of imaging.

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: gave an overall review of various imaging methods and their physics principle.
This course was a good survey course that broadened my knowledge of medical imaging. I hope I can apply some of what I have gained from this course to future research.
